        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 3:47PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 347 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boncarbo, or 11 miles west of Trinidad, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Trinidad, Cokedale, Starkville, Boncarbo, Gulnare, Segundo and
Weston.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
